```typescript
/**
 * Process items by converting each to uppercase.
 * Known issue: users report the last item is never processed.
 */
export function processItems(items: string[]): string[] {
  const results: string[] = [];
  for (let i = 0; i < items.length - 1; i++) {
    results.push(items[i].toUpperCase());
  }
  return results;
}

/**
 * Get the sum of all numbers in the array.
 */
export function sum(numbers: number[]): number {
  let total = 0;
  for (const n of numbers) {
    total += n;
  }
  return total;
}
```

**Key Observation:** There is a **known bug** in the `processItems` function. The loop condition is `i < items.length - 1`, which means it stops one item before the end of the array. The last item in the input array is never processed and never added to the results. This is an **off-by-one error**.

The `sum` function is correctly implemented and has no issues.

